Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.96,0:17:33.51,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,...透视血淋淋的野心 我们的希望再次被夺走\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}...through cold-blooded savagery, a beacon of hope has been taken from us.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.59,0:17:35.05,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,马丁魏尔事务所\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Law offices of Martin Vail.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.13,0:17:37.30,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 在看新闻吗? - 正在看\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- You got the news on, by any chance? - Yeah, we're watching it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.43,0:17:40.10,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,打电话到崔法官办公室\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}All right, I want you to call Sullivan in Judge Trotter's office.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.18,0:17:41.68,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,查出嫌犯下落再通知我\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Find out where they took him, and call me right back.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.76,0:17:42.81,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我在犯罪现场\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm at The Alibi.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.97,0:17:44.98,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,这案子很抢手\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- A lot of guys are gonna want this one. - Okay.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.94,0:17:47.56,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,警方的逮捕行动十分快速\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}The police have taken the first steps,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.65,0:17:50.02,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,而且破案决心坚定\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}acting with speed and determination with the arrest.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.21,0:18:12.71,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你将为他辩护吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Are you taking the Stampler case?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.80,0:18:14.92,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,抱歉 无可奉告\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Andy, I'm sorry. I can't talk to you about anything.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.34,0:18:17.47,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,十分感谢\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Thank you very much.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.55,0:18:20.30,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,再透露点信息好吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}When are you gonna talk?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.97,0:18:24.43,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 州检察长走了? - 走了\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- State's Attorney left yet? - Yeah. Yancy, no less.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.52,0:18:27.31,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 他来过? - 来过又走了 开闸\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- Yeah? P.D.? - Come and gone. Lockup!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.64,0:18:31.52,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 替我向你兄弟致意 - 没问题\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- Give my best to your brother. - Yeah, sure.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.36,0:18:35.65,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我想单独见他\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I'd like to see him alone, if I could.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.74,0:18:37.19,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我得把你关起来\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}All right, but I'm gonna have to lock you in.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.28,0:18:38.70,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,明白\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Understood.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.93,0:19:08.64,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你认识我吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}You know who I am?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.60,0:19:13.06,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,不认识\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, no. No, sir. No, I don't.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:14.07,0:19:18.57,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我叫马丁魏尔 所谓的大律师\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}My name is Martin Vail. I'm what you call a big-shot attorney.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.45,0:19:22.53,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我没钱\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't... I don't have no money.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.62,0:19:24.12,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我猜也是\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}No, I didn't think you did.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.20,0:19:26.83,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我愿意义务为你辩护\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm willing to take your case pro bono,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.91,0:19:30.83,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,也就是说我为你免费服务\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}which means you get all of my expertise and hard work for free.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.25,0:19:33.33,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,如果你不要我\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Or, if you want to,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.42,0:19:37.17,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你也能找年薪四万的公设律师\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}you could get the $40,000-a-year, court-appointed public defender,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.26,0:19:39.46,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你也能找年薪四万的公设律师 他会把你送进死牢\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}who will almost certainly escort you personally to death row.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.55,0:19:41.34,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,就看你的选择\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Your choice.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.43,0:19:43.59,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,不 先生 我...\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}No. No, sir. I...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.93,0:19:47.35,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我会感激你的帮忙\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I'd surely be grateful for anything you could do for me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.43,0:19:52.31,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,别客气 好吧 你的全名是?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}You're welcome. Now, your full name is?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.19,0:19:58.44,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,艾伦路克·史坦勒\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}My... Aaron Luke Stampler.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.78,0:20:02.07,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,史坦勒\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Stampler.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.53,0:20:06.66,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 你是肯塔基州人? - 没错 溪畔镇来的\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- You from Kentucky, Aaron? - Yes, sir. I'm from Creekside.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.83,0:20:09.79,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,上面写的?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Does it say that there?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.67,0:20:15.29,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你来芝加哥多久?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}How long you been here in Chicago?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.67,0:20:19.96,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我猜快两年了\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, two years next month, I think.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.84,0:20:23.72,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 有前科吗? - 没有\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- Have you ever been arrested? - No. No, sir.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.97,0:20:30.52,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你怎么会认识主教?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}So how do you know the Archbishop?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.81,0:20:38.06,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我在华克街上乞讨\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I was begging on the street up on Wacker Drive,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.48,0:20:43.65,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,罗主教开车经过\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Bishop Rushman came by in his Cadillac.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.82,0:20:47.82,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,看到我就停车了\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}He saw me, and he stopped.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.16,0:20:53.96,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,他带我到救主之家 我当辅祭\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}He took me into Savior House. I work as an altar boy.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.62,0:20:56.67,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,还参加诗班\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I sing in his choir.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.04,0:20:59.67,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你在救主之家待了多久?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}How long were you there at Savior House?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.17,0:21:01.76,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,一年半\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Year, year and a half.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.84,0:21:04.84,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,满十八岁就该离开\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}You're supposed to leave when you're 18,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.93,0:21:11.56,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,不过我满十九岁 主教还让我留下\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}but Bishop Rushman let me stay on way past my 19th birthday.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.18,0:21:15.02,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,他真是好心\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}That was nice of him.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.19,0:21:19.86,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,是的\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes. Yes, it was.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.86,0:21:26.32,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你为什么痛恨主教?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Aaron, did you have any reason to dislike the Archbishop?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.41,0:21:29.74,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,痛恨? 不 先生\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Dislike? No. No, sir.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.83,0:21:33.24,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,他就像个父亲\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}He was like a father to me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:33.33,0:21:34.96,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,是的 不过你...\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Yeah, but you...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.87,0:21:38.92,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我不知道该怎么说...\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}How do I say this? Were...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.00,0:21:42.84,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,他被谋杀时你也在吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Were you in the room when he was murdered?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.72,0:21:47.72,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你怎么解释?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}How can you explain that?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.01,0:21:52.06,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,房里有别人 魏先生\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}There was someone else in that room, Mr. Vail.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.31,0:21:56.31,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 有第三者? - 是的\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- There was a third person? - Yes, sir.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.39,0:21:57.35,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你跟警方说过?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Did you tell the police this?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.44,0:22:00.98,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,是的 但是他们不信\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes. Yes, I did, but they didn't believe me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.07,0:22:03.48,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你尽管跟我说\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}All right. Well, you tell me now.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:04.90,0:22:09.24,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我到罗主教的书房去还书\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I was returning a book to Bishop Rushman's library.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.53,0:22:14.74,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我听到吵声 于是走进睡房\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I heard noise, so I went back into his... In his bedroom.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.25,0:22:21.84,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,罗主教倒在地上\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Bishop Rushman was laying on the floor.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.92,0:22:24.92,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,到处都是血\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}There was blood all over everything.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.59,0:22:32.30,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我看到个影子 一个人正在靠近主教\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}And then I seen a shadow. I seen a person leaning over Bishop Rushman.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.68,0:22:39.31,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,他看到我就走过来 然后我就失去时间\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}He looked up and then he came at me, and that's when I lost time.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.94,0:22:43.40,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,"失去时间"是什么意思?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}What does that mean, "lost time"?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.11,0:22:47.36,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我失去知觉\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I blacked out.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.28,0:22:50.95,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,偶尔会这样\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}It just... It happens to me sometimes.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.70,0:22:56.87,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我...我常昏倒\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I just... I have spells.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.95,0:23:00.08,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,失去知觉后...\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I have spells. I lose time. I can't...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.63,0:23:03.67,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我什么都不记得\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I can't remember nothing.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.88,0:23:13.30,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你没做坏事为什么要逃跑?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Why did you run from the police, Aaron, if you didn't do anything wrong?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.80,0:23:15.10,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,当我...\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, when...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.18,0:23:18.27,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,当我醒来时 发现满身都是血\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}When I woke up, I was covered in blood.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.81,0:23:25.44,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我不知所措 我很害怕 听到警笛就跑\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I didn't know what to do. I got scared. I heard sirens, so I ran.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.52,0:23:29.07,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我知道这很难相信 我发誓...\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Look, I know how it looks, Mr. Vail, but I swear...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.15,0:23:31.07,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你不必说服我\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Yeah, I don't need you to try to convince me, Aaron.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.16,0:23:32.74,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,只要回答我的问题\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I just want you to answer my questions.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.82,0:23:35.37,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,不是我干的 你得相信\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}But I didn't do this. You've got to believe me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.45,0:23:38.04,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我不必相信 我也不管\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}No, I don't have to believe you. I don't care.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.12,0:23:39.16,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我是你的律师\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm your attorney,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:39.25,0:23:44.79,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,意味着我就是你父母 也是你的好友和神父\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}which means I am your mother, your father, best friend and your priest.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.34,0:23:49.01,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,除了我 不准跟别人谈\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}In other words, I don't want you talking to anyone but me from now on.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.09,0:23:51.97,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,警方 记者 狱友\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Not the cops, not the press, not the other guys in the cells here,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.05,0:23:55.80,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,谁都不行 你明白吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}nobody without my permission, you understand? Yeah?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.01,0:23:59.47,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 我明白 - 好的\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- Yes. Yes, I do. - All right.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:00.35,0:24:03.44,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,重要的是 你穿几号西装?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Now the important stuff. What's your suit size?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.02,0:24:08.36,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 什么? - 西装尺寸 三十八号?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- My what? - Suit size. What, you're about a 38?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.24,0:24:15.28,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我不晓得\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't know.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.37,0:24:18.74,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 大概三十八号长 - 好的\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- About a 38 long. - Okay.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.66,0:24:20.95,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,警方在教堂后面\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Stampler was flushed by the police{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.04,0:24:23.67,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,逮捕躲在灌木从里的史坦勒\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}from his hiding place in the bushes behind the cathedral.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.75,0:24:26.58,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,他逃到铁路调度场 就在麦考米站北面\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}The police chased him through the train yard, just north of McCormick Place,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.67,0:24:29.42,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,一列火车把他挡住\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}almost losing him as he scrambled over tracks{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:29.51,0:24:32.51,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,警方差点让他逃掉\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}before an oncoming train, separating him from the police.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.59,0:24:33.59,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,接下来的进展\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}In a later development,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.68,0:24:36.09,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,知名刑事辩护律师马丁魏尔\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}prominent local criminal defense attorney Martin Vail{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.18,0:24:39.10,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,据称曾前往警局会见嫌犯...\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}is believed to have visited Stampler at the Maxwell Street Precinct...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.18,0:24:43.10,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,警方在铁轨上和嫌犯展开追逐\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}After a brief chase across the rail yard behind Saint Michael's Cathedral,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:43.19,0:24:46.31,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,随后在隧道中将他逮捕\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Stampler was apprehended in a hole beneath train tracks.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:46.40,0:24:50.90,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 你将为他辩护吗? - 抱歉 我不能...\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- Are you gonna defend this man? - Andy, I'm sorry. I can't...{\r}
