Dialogue: 0,0:51:14.07,0:51:17.78,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,他们才不管 这群蠢猪不投票\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Truth is, they don't care. Dumb bastards don't even vote.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:17.86,0:51:20.11,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,只会吃喝拉睡\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}All they want to do is eat, sleep, watch TV{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.20,0:51:22.91,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,偶尔上老婆\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}and occasionally fuck their wives.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:22.99,0:51:24.91,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我们都该谢你了\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Guess we should all thank you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.87,0:51:27.54,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,别客气\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}You're welcome.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:28.83,0:51:31.50,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你得说点新鲜的\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}John, you need some new material.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.58,0:51:35.00,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,这些话我听过十遍\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I've heard this "great city" speech 10 times already.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.84,0:51:41.59,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,潘乔伊没有乖乖离开\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Your boy Pinero's not honoring his side of the deal.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:41.68,0:51:43.26,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,原来是为这件事?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Is that what this dinner was about? Pinero?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.35,0:51:44.85,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,不全然是\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}In part.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:45.85,0:51:50.10,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我跟他说过 他不是小孩 还有什么事?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I told him what the deal is. He's a grownup. What's the other part?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:52.19,0:51:53.73,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你的同事在调查\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I understand your assistant's been digging around{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:53.81,0:51:56.69,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,主教的财务\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}in the Archbishop's financial affairs.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:57.32,0:51:58.90,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,没错...\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Yeah. Well...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.12,0:52:07.29,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,南河那块地叫停\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}How much did you lose{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.37,0:52:10.46,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你损失多少?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}when he pulled the plug from South River, John?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.67,0:52:14.13,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,让我告诉你\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Let me tell you something.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.21,0:52:15.59,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你最好别惹\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}It's a mistake to stick your thumb{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.67,0:52:18.13,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,全市最有权力的人\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}in the eyes of the most powerful people in the city.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:18.21,0:52:20.80,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我并不是惹他们\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}It's not their eyes I'm aiming for.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:24.51,0:52:26.93,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,别找我麻烦 马提\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Do not fuck with me, Marty.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.95,0:52:43.36,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,地下水管又爆裂了\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Pipes are bursting again, John.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:00.76,0:53:04.09,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,芝加哥近年来最受瞩目的凶案\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}In the most anticipated murder trial in recent Chicago history,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:04.18,0:53:07.30,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,前州立检察官马丁魏尔\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}former State's Attorney prosecutor Martin Vail will lead{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:07.39,0:53:10.39,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,将为艾伦·史坦勒做开场申辩...\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}with his opening statement on behalf of Aaron Stampler...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.47,0:53:12.14,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,案件控诉方\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}The prosecution's case is headed{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:12.23,0:53:14.73,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,交由珍娜代理 她是...\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}by Assistant State's Attorney Janet Venable. Venable was...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:14.81,0:53:17.65,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,理察罗西曼是上帝之子\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Richard Rushman was a man of God.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.73,0:53:21.69,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,他为芝加哥人民付出一切\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}He spent his life giving to the people of Chicago.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.78,0:53:23.11,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,他鼓舞人心\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}He was a beacon of inspiration,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.20,0:53:26.20,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,他是精神领袖 也是优良市民\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}not only as a spiritual leader, but as a citizen.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:26.28,0:53:28.70,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,...明天进行开场申辩...\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}...will deliver his opening statement tomorrow on behalf of defendant...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.78,0:53:30.58,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我叫马丁魏尔\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}My name is Martin Vail,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:30.66,0:53:33.79,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我来的原因 各位来的原因\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}and the reason I'm here, and the reason you're here,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:33.87,0:53:36.62,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,是寻求真相\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}is to make sure that the whole truth is known.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:36.71,0:53:38.88,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我们先从\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Now, we can begin to learn the truth{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.96,0:53:42.05,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,控方不想听的事开始\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}by talking about what the prosecution does not want you to hear.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:42.13,0:53:46.55,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,别让被告无辜的表情骗倒\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Do not be fooled by the defendant's innocent appearance and demeanor.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.64,0:53:50.93,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,史艾伦对罗主教深恶痛绝\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Aaron Stampler sat in judgment of Archbishop Rushman{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:51.02,0:53:53.81,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,不但决定判他死刑\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}and determined that not only should he die,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:53.89,0:53:56.23,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,还以最残暴的手段杀害他\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}but he should die the most brutal way possible.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:56.31,0:53:58.56,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,艾伦在主教遇害后马上被捕\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Aaron was arrested within minutes of the Archbishop's death.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:53:58.65,0:54:00.73,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我们都在电视看到\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}We all know that. We all saw it on television.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.82,0:54:04.40,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,为什么? 因为他正好在场\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}But why? Because he was convenient.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:04.49,0:54:07.41,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,警方受到压力要马上破案\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Because there was enormous pressure on the police to solve this crime.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.49,0:54:11.91,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,证据显示史艾伦 跟踪 偷袭\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}The evidence will show that Aaron Stampler stalked, ambushed{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:11.99,0:54:14.25,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,并残忍地谋杀这名伟人\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}and savagely murdered this great man.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:14.33,0:54:16.16,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,控方不想让你们知道\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}The prosecution does not want you to hear{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:16.25,0:54:18.12,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,另有离奇失踪的\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}about the other altar boys in the church choir{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.21,0:54:20.00,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,其他辅祭\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}who have mysteriously disappeared.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.09,0:54:21.71,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,在看过所有的证据后 各位\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}At the close of evidence, ladies and gentlemen,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.80,0:54:24.92,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你们将知道艾伦\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}you will learn that Aaron Stampler had everything he needed{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.01,0:54:26.67,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,有完美的暗杀条件\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}for the perfect assassination.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:26.76,0:54:32.26,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,史艾伦用利刃\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Using this knife, Aaron Stampler repeatedly stabbed{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.35,0:54:37.06,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,重覆刺向主教的胸口 他的生殖器及双眼\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}at the Archbishop's chest, his genitals, his eyes.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.14,0:54:40.56,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,控方不想让各位知道\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}They don't want you to hear that the Archbishop made investments{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.65,0:54:42.65,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,但罗主教曾为罗马教会投资\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}on behalf of the Roman Catholic Church{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:42.73,0:54:45.86,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,这些投资造成巨大损失\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}and that those investments resulted in huge losses{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.95,0:54:48.07,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,他的投资合伙人有权有势\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}for some very, very powerful people.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:48.16,0:54:51.78,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,控方不想让你知道\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}They don't want you to hear about the 20 death threats this year alone{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.87,0:54:54.12,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,主教曾收到二十次死亡威胁\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}that the Archbishop received prior to his death.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.20,0:54:58.37,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,控方也不想说出被告的动机\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}And they really don't want you to hear about their theory of motive.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.46,0:55:00.71,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,理由很简单\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}And why is that? Very simple.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.17,0:55:05.00,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,他们找不到动机\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}They don't have one.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.13,0:55:10.89,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,伍警探 你能解释\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Inspector Woodside, can you explain to the court{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:10.97,0:55:12.97,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,球鞋哪儿来的?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}where these sneakers came from?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.06,0:55:16.47,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,这是被告被捕时穿的\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}They were taken off the defendant when he was apprehended.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.56,0:55:19.64,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,鞋上血迹检验结果是什么?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}And what was the result of the bloodstain analysis done on them?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.73,0:55:22.36,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,检验结果是人血\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}The result of the analysis proved to be human blood{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:22.44,0:55:24.98,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,符合罗主教血型\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}matching the blood type and DNA characteristics{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.07,0:55:26.53,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,及DNA特徵\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}of Archbishop Rushman.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:26.61,0:55:29.32,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,尸体周围的带血鞋印呢?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}What do the bloody footprints surrounding the body tell you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:29.41,0:55:32.41,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,凶手在尸体周围\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}The killer left a pattern of bloody footprints{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:32.49,0:55:34.03,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,留下带血的鞋印\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}around the area of the struggle,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:34.12,0:55:37.00,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,弄得房间里到处都是\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}as indicated by the spread of blood through the room.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.08,0:55:38.71,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,是不是 检察官?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}All right, yes or no, Inspector?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.79,0:55:42.25,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,主教房里是否可能有第三者?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Could there have been a third person in the Archbishop's quarters that morning?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:42.33,0:55:43.92,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,没办法证明有\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}There is no evidence to suggest that.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.00,0:55:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,也没办法证明没有\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}But there's no evidence to prove there wasn't.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:46.26,0:55:47.34,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,没错\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}No.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:47.42,0:55:49.51,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,死者挣扎后发生什么?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}And after the struggle, what happened then?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:49.59,0:55:53.09,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,分析得出凶手在毁尸时\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, analysis suggests that the killer was startled during the mutilation{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:53.18,0:55:55.64,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,被惊动跑到楼下\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}and ran from the bedroom down the stairs.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:55.72,0:56:01.44,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,警探 是否有可能 真的凶手 这名第三者\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Is it possible, Inspector, that the real killer, a third person,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.15,0:56:03.60,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,也许聪明到\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}who maybe was smart enough{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:03.69,0:56:08.03,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,刻意避开一滩滩的鲜血\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}not to tramp a whole freeway of blood through the whole place here,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.11,0:56:11.53,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,第三者也可能趁被告昏倒时\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}couldn't this third person have placed the defendant's prints{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:11.61,0:56:14.03,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,将被告指纹印在凶刀上?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}on the knife while he was passed out?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.12,0:56:16.03,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,什么都有可能\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Mr. Vail, anything is possible.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:16.12,0:56:19.50,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,被害人很明显受到多处刀伤\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}So, clearly, the victim suffered a great number of stab wounds?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:19.58,0:56:23.37,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,是的 共有78处 他想自卫\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, he did, 78. He tried to defend himself.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:23.46,0:56:26.04,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,因此手掌手臂皆有刀伤\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}And that explains the cuts on the hands and the forearms.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.13,0:56:29.13,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,大夫 你是否无法确定\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Doctor, isn't it a fact that you can't be sure{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:29.21,0:56:35.05,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,78处刀伤都是一人下手?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}whether more than one person inflicted these 78 stab and incise wounds?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:35.14,0:56:37.97,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,可能不只一人 但我怀疑\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}That's true, Counselor. It could've been more than one person, but I doubt it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.06,0:56:40.77,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,根据刀伤看来\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}From your analysis of the knife wounds, Dr. Weil,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:40.85,0:56:44.23,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你认为凶手惯用左手或右手?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}do you have an opinion whether the killer was left-handed or right-handed?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:44.31,0:56:47.07,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,喉部和胸部刀伤的切入角度\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, the incise wound to the throat and most of the chest wounds{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.15,0:56:50.36,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,显示很可能是左撇子\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}were made from an angle that strongly suggests that a left-handed person{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:50.44,0:56:51.53,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,持刀杀人\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}was using the knife.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.61,0:56:53.70,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,被告是左撇子吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}To your knowledge, is the defendant left-handed?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:53.78,0:56:54.91,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,是的\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, he is.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.99,0:56:57.24,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,右撇子有可能故意\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, then it's possible that a right-handed person{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:57.33,0:57:01.20,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,用左手造成刀伤吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}could've deliberately used his left hand to inflict some of these wounds.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:01.29,0:57:02.71,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,是有可能\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, I suppose that is possible.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:02.79,0:57:05.08,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,因此应该能假设\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Then it would be reasonable to assume{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.17,0:57:08.63,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,现场有第三者?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}that there was, in fact, a third person there at the crime scene?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:08.71,0:57:11.63,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,不太合理 但有可能\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Reasonable, no. But it is possible.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.72,0:57:13.47,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,开场申辩后接着是...\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Then following opening statements,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:13.55,0:57:15.47,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,控方证人\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}it was a day of strong and detailed testimony{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.55,0:57:17.60,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,库克郡证物组伍警探\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}from the prosecution's first witnesses,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.68,0:57:20.01,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,和万验尸官的\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Cook County Forensics Chief Harvey Woodside{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:20.10,0:57:22.52,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,有力证词\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}and Cook County Medical Examiner Emile Weil.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.60,0:57:24.69,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,接着是被告辩护律师\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}It was also a day of tough cross-examination{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.77,0:57:25.94,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,马丁魏尔\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}of Woodside and Weil{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:26.02,0:57:28.11,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,对两位证人提出\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}by Stampler defense attorney Martin Vail.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.19,0:57:29.65,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,尖锐的盘诘...\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}By most accounts, though, the prosecution...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.19,0:57:31.90,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,石队长 感谢你\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Captain Stenner, I would like to thank you{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:31.99,0:57:33.95,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,今天抽空前来\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}for all the time you've given us today,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.03,0:57:36.32,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我想请你\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}but, finally, I would like to turn your attention{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.41,0:57:39.78,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,谈谈主教胸口刻的图样\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}to the symbol carved into the Archbishop's chest.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:39.87,0:57:43.29,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你可以为我们解释吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Now would you please tell the jury about that, Captain?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.37,0:57:49.04,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,好的 主教的胸口刻有\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes. The letter and the numbers B32.156{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.13,0:57:50.92,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,字母和号码 "B32156"\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}were carved into the Archbishop's chest.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:51.00,0:57:52.55,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,这组码号\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}What you just described,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.63,0:57:55.26,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,是否有符合的资料?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}have you been able to find an identical reference anywhere?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:55.34,0:57:56.97,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,应该有\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I believe so, yes.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.05,0:58:02.81,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,B32156的号码是...\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}The symbol B32.156 is actually catalog code for a book{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.89,0:58:06.98,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,位于教堂地下室私人阅览室里一本书的序号\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}discovered in a private reading room located in the church basement.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.06,0:58:11.94,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,在这组号码中 B32是指\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}That particular number, the B32 part, refers to a book,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.03,0:58:14.99,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,霍桑的 "猩红字母" 这本书\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}The Scarlet Letter by Nathaniel Hawthorne.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:15.07,0:58:20.95,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,当我们翻到156页 发现一行句子被人画线\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}When we opened the book to Page 156, we discovered an underlined passage.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.74,0:58:26.46,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,请你读出这行画线的句子\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Would you please read this underlined passage to the court?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:29.38,0:58:32.34,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,"没有人能够长期地\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}"No man, for any considerable period,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:32.42,0:58:36.42,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,"以虚假的面具面对众人\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}"can wear one face to himself and another to the multitude{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:36.51,0:58:40.60,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,"而最终不会对真相 感到迷惑"\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}"without finally getting bewildered as to which may be the true."{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:41.56,0:58:43.06,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,谢谢你\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Thank you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:46.98,0:58:48.94,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,这段话是什么意思?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}What does that passage mean to you, Captain?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:49.02,0:58:51.90,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,抗议 他只是警察 不是文学教授\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Objection. He's a policeman, not an English professor.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.98,0:58:54.73,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,他的诠释纯属猜臆与案情无关\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}His interpretation would be speculative and irrelevant.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.82,0:58:56.61,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,她不是要求专家意见\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I didn't hear her ask for an expert opinion.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:56.70,0:58:58.78,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,证人请回答\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}The witness can answer.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:59.91,0:59:02.03,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,对我来说很简单\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, to me, it's simple.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.12,0:59:05.04,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,凶手认为受害人两面派\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}The killer thought that his victim was two-faced,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:05.12,0:59:06.58,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,言行不一致\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}dishonest in some way.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.66,0:59:08.50,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,以你的经验判断\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}In your experience, Captain,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:08.58,0:59:12.38,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,凶手是否可能蓄意留下线索?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}do killers ever intentionally leave clues to their motive?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:12.46,0:59:14.88,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,不常见 但是有前例\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Not often, but it happens.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.89,0:59:22.14,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,谢了\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Thanks.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:22.93,0:59:24.97,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 谢了 老兄 - 不客气\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- Thanks, man. - Yeah, sure.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:25.43,0:59:28.02,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你在书上画线吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Did you underline that book?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.10,0:59:30.69,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 什么? - 你在书上画线吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- Did I what? - Did you underline that book?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:30.77,0:59:33.86,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 不是 魏先生 - 不是?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- No. No, Mr. Vail. - No?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.94,0:59:37.61,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我从来没翻过"猩红字母"\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}No. Mr. Vail. I never even opened The Scarlet Letter.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:37.69,0:59:40.70,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我不喜欢霍桑的书\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't like Hawthorne.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.78,0:59:43.24,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,高中时看过他的一本书\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I tried to read that one about the house with the seven somethings{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:43.33,0:59:46.41,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,可是读不到十页就看不下去了\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}in high school. I couldn't even get past Page 10.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.16,0:59:52.25,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,又不是只有我向罗主教借过书\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I mean, I weren't the only one using Bishop Rushman's library.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.63,0:59:55.00,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,大家都向他借过书\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}You know what? Everybody borrowed books from Bishop Rushman.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.09,0:59:56.34,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,他鼓励\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}He encouraged it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.42,0:59:58.51,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,辅祭和教会职员看书\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}His altar boys and staff, everyone was in there.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:58.59,0:59:59.88,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,警卫?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Guard?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:01.84,1:00:03.26,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,谢了\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Thanks.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.35,1:00:12.65,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你真是契而不舍\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}You don't give up, do you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.36,1:00:19.99,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你知道什么吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}So you didn't know anything about that?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.07,1:00:22.32,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 不知道 - 它造成的冲击...\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- No. - What about the impact of...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:22.41,1:00:25.12,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我现在没空 我的秘书会跟你联络\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Look, I can't talk to you right now. My office will call you, all right?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.20,1:00:27.49,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 好吧 谢了 - 别客气 再见\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- Yeah. Thanks. - Okay, bye. Yeah, I'll see you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.33,1:00:31.25,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 再见 - 再见\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- Bye. - Bye.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:38.38,1:00:40.05,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,这到底怎么回事?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}What the fuck happened in there?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:41.09,1:00:44.34,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我猜结果不是"8"是"B"\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I guess that eight was a "B" after all.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.39,1:00:48.51,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,这不好笑 我们快输了\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}You think this is funny? We're losing this case.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.85,1:00:51.98,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,怎么回事 汤米? 怎么会弄错?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}What the hell happened, Tommy? How could you have missed that?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.06,1:00:53.14,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,马提 他们有五十人\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Marty, there are 50 of them,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:53.23,1:00:54.98,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,和全警局在调查\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}plus the entire Chicago Police Department.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:55.06,1:00:57.52,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,谁知道教堂有私人阅览室?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}How was I to know he had a private reading room in the church basement?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.61,1:00:59.36,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 那是你的工作 - 你要我的工作吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- It's your job to know. - Fuck, Marty, you want my job?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:59.44,1:01:00.94,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,不 我要你尽职!\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}No. I want you to do your fucking job!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.03,1:01:02.65,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,马提 冷静点\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Marty, come on.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:03.74,1:01:05.36,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我靠第三者理论为这场官司辩护\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm working on a third-man defense here.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.45,1:01:06.99,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你知道吗? 你拎得清吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Do you know that? Have you figured that out yet?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.08,1:01:09.58,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,但没有第三者 为什么?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't have a third man. You know why I don't have a third man?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:09.66,1:01:12.12,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,因为你没找到他!\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}'Cause you can't fucking find him! That's why.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.21,1:01:14.08,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,穷孩子这么难找吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Is it that hard to find one indigent kid?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.17,1:01:17.25,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,也许已经找到凶手\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Look, maybe we already got the kid who did this.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.67,1:01:21.01,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你得考虑可能是他干的\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}We have to at least consider the possibility that he did it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.09,1:01:22.55,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,所有证据都把矛头指向他\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}All the hard evidence is pointing towards him,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.63,1:01:24.05,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你拒绝看所有证据\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}and you keep refusing to even look at it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.13,1:01:27.97,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我没有! 我认为凶手不是他!\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm not refusing to look at anything! I don't think he did it!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:28.72,1:01:29.85,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,听好\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Look, you two,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:29.93,1:01:31.97,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我们忙活那么多天 但什么都没有!\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}we're up there in a couple of days, and we got dick!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.06,1:01:34.60,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我要你们再努力点\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}So I wish the two of you'd do your fucking goddamn jobs, all right?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.69,1:01:36.02,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,他妈的!\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Fuck!{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:49.62,1:01:52.54,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你在这里一定很难过\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}It must have been hard for you to come here to Chicago.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:52.62,1:01:54.66,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,无亲无故\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}You didn't know anybody.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:55.46,1:01:56.96,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,没...没错\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}No. Nobody.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:57.71,1:01:59.63,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你有钱吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Didn't have any money?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:01.13,1:02:02.63,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,没...没有\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}No, nothing.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:04.05,1:02:08.64,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我想谈谈你女友琳达 行吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I want to talk more about your girlfriend, Linda, now. Can we, Aaron?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:10.47,1:02:12.52,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 不行 - 为什么?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- No. - Why not?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:17.10,1:02:18.27,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,艾伦\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Aaron.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.86,1:02:26.53,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,对不起\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm sorry.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:28.78,1:02:31.83,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,可以改天再谈吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Do you think we can do this later?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:31.91,1:02:37.75,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 我想继续谈下去 - 我只是有点...有点累\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- No, I want to stay with this for a minute. - I'm just feeling a little tired.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.83,1:02:41.34,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我知道 谈起琳达你为何生气?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I know. Why does talking about Linda Forbes upset you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:43.80,1:02:45.21,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,没有\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}It doesn't.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.38,1:02:49.55,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我只是现在不想谈\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I just don't want to talk about it right now.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.68,1:02:54.72,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 为什么? 你还好吧? - 不好 我的头好痛\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- Why not? Are you all right? - No, my head hurts.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:56.35,1:02:58.98,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,抱歉 让我弄好它\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Okay, okay, I'm sorry. Let me just fix this.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:04.53,1:03:06.28,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你知道能拿这个来干嘛吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Hey, you know what I can do with this thing?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.36,1:03:08.74,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,他妈的 我怎么知道?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}No, how the fuck should I know?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.08,1:03:13.53,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,老天\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Jesus Christ.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:22.71,1:03:23.88,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,艾伦?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Aaron?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.56,1:03:34.68,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,什么?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}What?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.39,1:03:38.23,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你在说什么?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}What were you saying?{\r}
