Dialogue: 0,1:44:35.85,1:44:37.93,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,很可能身在现场\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}his body could be present at a homicide{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:44:38.02,1:44:40.44,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,却一点也不记得\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}and yet his mind would be unable to recall it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:44:40.85,1:44:43.36,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 怎么会呢? - 以精神分析角度来看\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- And how is that possible? - The neurological mechanism{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:44:43.44,1:44:46.19,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,被告小时候\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}that would make this possible began with the early abuse{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:44:46.28,1:44:48.03,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,曾遭父亲虐待\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}suffered at the hands of his father.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:44:48.11,1:44:50.53,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,为求防卫 他的精神分裂\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}In defense, Aaron's psyche splintered{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:44:50.61,1:44:53.57,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,造成双重性格\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}and helped him to create two separate personalities.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:44:53.66,1:44:55.70,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 庭上 - 魏先生\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- Your Honor. - I didn't say it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:44:55.79,1:44:58.45,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 不是我说的... - 我警告你两次\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- I did not say it... - You've been warned twice now.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:44:58.54,1:45:00.50,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你还想问吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Do you really wanna pursue this line of questioning?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:00.58,1:45:04.04,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,请你慎重考虑再回答\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}And I suggest you think long and hard before answering.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:06.71,1:45:09.26,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,庭上 这是最后一个问题\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Your Honor, just one last question.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:14.18,1:45:16.22,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,好的 尹医师\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}All right, Dr. Arrington,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:17.68,1:45:22.64,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你认为艾伦有能力谋杀吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}in your opinion, is Aaron Stampler capable of murder?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:22.73,1:45:24.56,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,不能 他受创太深\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}No, he is not. He is far too traumatized{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:24.65,1:45:26.82,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,无法表现愤怒和挫折感\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}to express normal anger and frustration.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:26.90,1:45:28.98,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,他压抑情感\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}He keeps his emotions repressed,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:29.07,1:45:31.65,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,所以他创造洛伊 这样有能力犯案\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}which is why he created Roy, who is capable of such a crime.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:31.74,1:45:34.24,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 抗议 庭上 - 够了\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- Objection, Your Honor. - That's enough, Mr. Vail.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:34.37,1:45:38.03,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,最后的证词陪审团不必考虑\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}The jury will disregard this witness' last statement, as will the court.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:38.12,1:45:39.41,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 谢谢你 - 检察官\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- Thank you very much. - Madam Prosecutor,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:39.50,1:45:42.04,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 你要盘诘吗? - 当然要\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- do you wish to cross? - You bet I do.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:44.42,1:45:47.84,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,既然你违抗法官指示提出来\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Since you brought it up, against the instructions of the court,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:47.92,1:45:49.34,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我很好奇\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm curious to know,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:49.42,1:45:52.84,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,请问你是多重性格症专家吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}is multiple personality disorder your primary area of expertise?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:52.93,1:45:54.97,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,不是我的专攻\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}It's not my primary field, no.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:55.05,1:45:58.60,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你是犯罪心理专家吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Is forensic psychiatry your primary area of expertise?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:45:59.10,1:46:01.60,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 我是精神心理学家 - 明白了\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- No, I'm a neuropsychologist. - I see.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:02.02,1:46:04.94,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,原来你没有犯罪心理学经验\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}So you have no forensic experience,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:05.02,1:46:08.61,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你其实比较偏向学术研究\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}and you're more of, let's say, an academic?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:09.98,1:46:13.28,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,那我问个学术性问题\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Then you will forgive this rather academic question.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:13.95,1:46:16.99,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我在开车时被人抄车\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm driving in my car, somebody cuts me off.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:17.07,1:46:19.03,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我很想杀他\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I think to myself, "I could just kill that guy,"{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:19.12,1:46:20.70,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,但不会真杀他吧?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}but I don't, now do I?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:20.79,1:46:22.62,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 希望如此 - 没错\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- I would hope not. - That's right.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:22.71,1:46:26.37,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我们都会受到挫折\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Things happen to us. People wrong us,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:26.46,1:46:28.92,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,但不会创造双重性格\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}but we don't all go around inventing psychopaths{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:29.00,1:46:31.00,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,来干坏事 是吗 医生?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}to do our dirty work for us, now, do we, Doctor?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:31.09,1:46:34.26,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我没说你有双重性格\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm not suggesting you suffer from multiple personality, Miss Venable.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:34.34,1:46:37.22,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 我是说史先生有 - 我们都听到\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- I'm saying Mr. Stampler does. - Yes, I know. We heard.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:39.18,1:46:43.48,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你还说你见过这个...\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}You have also testified that you have met this...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:43.56,1:46:44.89,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,他叫什么?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}What was his name again?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:44.98,1:46:46.39,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 洛伊 - 姓?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- Roy. - Roy what?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:46.98,1:46:49.23,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 他没有姓 - 是吗\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- He didn't give a last name. - I see.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:49.32,1:46:53.40,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,洛伊告诉你主教是他杀的吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Did this Roy tell you that he had murdered the Archbishop?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:53.49,1:46:56.11,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,魏先生与他独处 但我一往窗里看\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Mr. Vail was alone with him at the time. I was watching through the window,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:56.20,1:46:59.37,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,一进屋就看到洛伊\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}but soon after that I was in the room and saw both Roy{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:46:59.45,1:47:01.79,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,变回艾伦的情形\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}and his transformation back to Aaron.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:02.66,1:47:08.25,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,这个人出现时你有录影吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Did you happen to tape this appearance of Aaron...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:09.67,1:47:14.17,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,对不起 我不习惯用这个的名字\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm sorry. I am sorry. I just cannot get used to this name.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:14.26,1:47:16.67,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 洛伊 - 你有录吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- Roy. - Did you?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:18.47,1:47:21.18,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 没有 录影带坏了 - 坏了?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- No, the tape was off. - Off?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:23.39,1:47:28.39,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,这么说你根本就没有他出现的记录\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}So you have no record whatsoever of his appearance.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:28.69,1:47:29.94,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 没有 - 没有\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- No. - No.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:32.36,1:47:35.11,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,艾伦能分辨是非吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Does Aaron Stampler know the difference between right and wrong?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:35.19,1:47:36.24,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,他能\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, he does.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:36.32,1:47:39.07,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,如果史艾伦残杀主教...\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}If Aaron Stampler butchered the Archbishop, would he know...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:39.16,1:47:40.28,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,抗议 庭上\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Objection, Your Honor.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:40.37,1:47:43.74,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,如果艾伦谋杀主教\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}If Aaron Stampler murdered the Archbishop,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:43.83,1:47:48.25,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 他会知道这是非法吗? - 知道 但不是他杀的...\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- would he know he'd broken the law? - Yes, he would, but it wasn't Aaron...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:48.37,1:47:52.46,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我明白 是洛伊杀的\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, I know, Doctor. It was Roy.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:55.76,1:47:59.05,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,好了 我问完了\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}That's all. No further questions, Your Honor.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:47:59.18,1:48:00.64,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,证人可以离席\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Witness may step down.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:48:00.72,1:48:03.72,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,检控官 我愿意同意你\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Miss Venable, if you would like to re-open the Prosecution's case{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:48:03.81,1:48:05.31,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,传唤立精神科医师\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}and call the State's psychiatrist,{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:48:05.39,1:48:08.56,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 我同意其作证 - 不 我...\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- I will certainly agree to it. - No, I...{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:48:08.64,1:48:10.23,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,没有这必要 庭上\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't think that's necessary, Your Honor.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:48:10.31,1:48:12.06,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我们都了解了\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I think we all get the picture here.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:48:12.90,1:48:16.32,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,魏先生 你可以继续吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Mr. Vail, are you ready to proceed?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:48:19.11,1:48:20.91,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你要休庭吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Would you like a recess?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:26.22,1:49:27.31,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,洛伊?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Roy?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:28.81,1:49:29.97,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,艾伦\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Aaron.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:33.94,1:49:36.02,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,请告诉大家\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Could you tell us a little about your relationship{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:36.11,1:49:37.98,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你和罗主教的关系\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}with Archbishop Rushman?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:38.57,1:49:43.28,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,他就像个父亲 我很敬爱他\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, he was like a father to me. I loved him very much.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:43.36,1:49:45.07,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你为什么敬爱他?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Why did you love him?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:45.66,1:49:46.82,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,为什么?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Why?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:48.12,1:49:52.08,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,他救了我的命\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, he saved my life.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:52.33,1:49:57.29,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,只有他不把我当个废物\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}He was the only person who ever treated me like I was worth anything.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:49:57.67,1:50:00.42,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,别牢骚了 你这孬种 当个男子汉\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Stop your whining, you little girl. Be a man.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:04.18,1:50:07.51,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我们都看到那卷录影带\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Now, we've all seen that tape that you were in, Aaron.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:08.47,1:50:09.85,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你对此有何感觉?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}How did that make you feel?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:09.93,1:50:12.73,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你对罗主教的想法有改变吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Did it change your feelings about Archbishop Rushman?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:13.02,1:50:14.02,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,没有\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}No.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:15.40,1:50:18.19,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,他是个好人\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}He was a wonderful man.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:18.27,1:50:19.90,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,他逼你做那种事\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}So you didn't feel anger towards him{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:19.98,1:50:22.36,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你不生气吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}about being forced to perform in that tape?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:23.03,1:50:26.86,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,不 他对我很好\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}No, he did everything for me.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:27.03,1:50:30.12,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我只能用这种方法报答他\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}There wasn't nothing else I could do for him, and he needed it.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:30.20,1:50:32.45,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你认识洛伊这人吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Do you know someone named Roy?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:35.50,1:50:36.87,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,不认识\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}No, I don't.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:37.63,1:50:40.42,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你听到尹医师说\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}You heard Dr. Arrington's testimony about{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:40.50,1:50:42.76,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我们目睹的事\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}what she and I saw there at the jail.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:43.22,1:50:46.05,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,艾伦 事情很诡异 你记得吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Aaron, some pretty strange things going on there. Do you remember?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:46.14,1:50:48.51,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,我都听说过 不过我不记得\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I heard what she said, but I don't remember any of that.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:48.60,1:50:50.43,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 毫无印象? - 没有\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- No recollection? - No, sir.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:50.51,1:50:52.85,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,罗主教是你杀的吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Did you kill Archbishop Rushman?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:50:54.85,1:50:56.73,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,不 不是我杀的\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}No, sir, I did not.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:02.69,1:51:03.78,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,谢谢\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Thank you.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:06.61,1:51:08.07,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,该你问\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Your witness.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:15.58,1:51:18.21,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,史先生 你要喝水吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Mr. Stampler, would you like some water?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:22.21,1:51:24.76,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,- 不...不用 - 你确定吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}- No, ma'am. - You sure?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:26.43,1:51:28.47,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,确定 谢谢你\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, ma'am. Yes, ma'am.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:36.39,1:51:40.52,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,史先生 你相信主教有戴面具吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Mr. Stampler, did you believe that the Archbishop wore masks?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:43.65,1:51:45.78,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,抱歉 你说什么?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm sorry, what did you say?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:46.07,1:51:50.20,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,你觉得他表里不一吗?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Do you think he acted one way in public and another way in private?{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:51.24,1:51:53.24,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,不...我不觉得\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}No, I didn't think that.{\r}
Dialogue: 0,1:51:54.08,1:51:56.45,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,所以你在霍桑书上画线?\NIsn’t that why you underlined the Hawthorne passage?
Dialogue: 0,1:51:59.00,1:52:00.42,Default,,0000,0000,0015,,史先生?\N{\fntahoma\fs11\1c&H00FFFF&}Mr. Stampler?{\r}
